-- China May Allow Insurers to Invest in Index Futures, Securities Times Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-22T22:40:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/china-may-allow-insurers-to-invest-in-index-futures-securities-times-says.html

          
          
             China may allow insurance companies
to invest in stock index futures, the Securities Times reported
today, citing an unidentified insurance company.  
 Insurers would be allowed to invest in index futures to
hedge against risks and not for speculation, the Shenzhen-based
newspaper reported.  
